\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Telemundo will provide Spanish-language coverage beginning at 1 p.m.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2061, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telemundo\", \"score\": 0.999999999389729, \"rank\": 5.801599284205651e-10, \"text\": \"Telemundo\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telemundo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telemundo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Primetime coverage will begin at 7:30 p.m. ET/PT on NBC and Peacock.\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2186, \"end\": 2189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.6729372949236545, \"rank\": 0.48602180786285026, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2194, \"end\": 2201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.999998082730618, \"rank\": 1.9172721579446386e-06, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The plans for the Opening Ceremony are unlike any other.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2222, \"end\": 2238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999966738992788, \"rank\": 3.1604435951792907e-06, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 organizers are turning one of the world's most famous waterways, the River Seine, into the world's biggest theatrical stage.\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2341, \"end\": 2352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of walking into a stadium, a four-mile-long flotilla of nearly 100 boats will carry thousands of athletes from more than 200 countries past hundreds of thousands of spectators seated on the banks of the Seine.\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2608, \"end\": 2613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.1504207472328476e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was announced in March that Emmy Award-winning talk show host and Grammy Award-winning artistKelly Clarksonand Pro Football Hall of Fame quarterback and two-time Super Bowl championPeyton Manningwill join two-time Sports Emmy Award-winner and NBC Olympics primetime hostMike Tiricotohost NBCU's coverage of the Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2862, \"end\": 2874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}, {\"begin\": 2907, \"end\": 2911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 2930, \"end\": 2946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999966738992788, \"rank\": 3.1604435951792907e-06, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Joining Kelly, Peyton, and Mike from a different vantage point will beTODAYShow hostsSavannah GuthrieandHoda Kotb.\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 3062, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2963, \"end\": 2969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.26477077595747e-15, \"text\": \"Peyton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"***  In Paris this summer, the world's greatest athletes will compete against the backdrop of one of the most beautiful cities in the world where the modern Olympic Games were conceived 130 years ago.\", \"from\": 3064, \"to\": 3264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3072, \"end\": 3077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2417028102834347e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be the third time Paris has hosted the Olympics (1900 and 1924), tying London for the most as a Summer Games host.\", \"from\": 3265, \"to\": 3389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3293, \"end\": 3298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2417028102834347e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3346, \"end\": 3352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999994608198538, \"rank\": 5.376820565636919e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles (1932, 1984) will tie those two cities when it hosts the first Summer Games in the U.S. in 32 years in 2028.\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3390, \"end\": 3401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999427018, \"rank\": 5.7442866888050285e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris organizers are reimagining the Games to make them more accessible to the public and to showcase their city to the world.\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3516, \"end\": 3521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2417028102834347e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a first, competitions will be held amidst iconic Parisian landmarks - beach volleyball at the Eiffel Tower, equestrian at the Palace of Versailles, and urban sports at Place de la Concorde.\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3814, \"end\": 3834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.002453575045188e-16, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The surfing competition will take place nearly 10,000 miles from Paris in Tahiti, a part of French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 3836, \"to\": 3945, \"entitie